<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE MOVIE CHART: FILMS GOING INTO PRODUCTION: 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By David Pecchia 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Love Field (Midge Sanford/Sarah Pillsbury). Shooting in North Carolina. 
Michelle Pfeiffer's a young Southern woman who travels to our nation's capital 
after JFK's assassination. 
</P>
<P>
En route she meets and establishes a relationship with a black man. Producers 
Midge Sanford and Sarah Pillsbury. Director Jonathan Kaplan. Screenwriter Don 
Roos. 
</P>
<P>
Sleeping With the Enemy (Fox). Shooting in North and South Carolina. Julia 
Roberts stars in this thriller as a woman who suffers much after falling for 
the wrong man. The Nancy Price novel comes to life under the direction of "The 
Stepfather's" Joseph Ruben. Executive producer Jeffrey Chernov. Producer 
Leonard Goldberg. Screenwriters Lloyd Fonvielle, Ron Bass and Bruce Joel Rubin. 
Also stars Patrick Bergin and Kevin Anderson. 
</P>
<P>
The Taking of Beverly Hills (Nelson). Shooting in L.A. and Mexico City. 
"Wiseguy" heartthrob Ken Wahl stars as a high-profile pro quarterback who finds 
himself partnered with a crooked cop during the biggest heist Beverly Hills has 
ever witnessed. Producer David Giler. Director Sidney J. Furie. Screenwriters 
Rick Natkin, David Fuller and David Burke. Also stars Harley Kozak and Matt 
Frewer. 
</P>
<P>
Until the End of the World (Road Movies/Argos Films). Shooting in Italy, 
France, U.S.S.R., China, etc. "Wings of Desire" director Wim Wenders' mammoth 
project (shot in 65mm) stars William Hurt and Max Von Sydow and purports to be 
a Hitchcockian love story set a decade hence. Producers Jonathan Taplin and 
Anatole Dauman. Screenwriters Wenders and Peter Carey. Late '90 release. David 
Pecchia 
</P>
