<BYLINE>
<P>
By John M. Wilson 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
While "House Party" took off surprisingly well, a number of recent releases 
with bigger budgets, stars and profiles haven't. Among the more disappointing: 
"Revenge," $15.3 million, 38 days; "Stella," $19.4 million, 52 days; "Men Don't 
Leave," $6 million, 52 days; "Blue Steel," $5.6 million, 10 days. And despite 
all the Rob Lowe publicity, the opening of "Bad Influence" hasn't been a 
thriller -- a modest $10 million on 1,300 screens in its first 17 days. John M. 
Wilson 
