<HEADLINE>
<P>
JAPANESE CLIMBER DIES IN FALL ON NEPAL'S MT. PUMORI 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
KATMANDU, Nepal 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The leader of a Japanese climbing expedition died when he fell into a crevasse 
in the Himalayas, Nepal's tourism ministry said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
It said Yoshikuni Mori, a 21-year-old student from Tokushima University, fell 
into a 525-foot-deep crevasse Wednesday while climbing the 23,494-foot Mt. 
Pumori. 
</P>
<P>
His body was found at an altitude of 20,300 feet. The team abandoned the 
attempt on Pumori. 
</P>
