<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN KILLED WHEN CAR SLAMS INTO TREE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A motorist was killed early Saturday when his speeding car failed to negotiate 
a bend in Jesmond Dene Road north of Escondido and slammed broadside into an 
oak tree, a California Highway Patrol spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
Dead at the scene of the accident was Terry L. Johnson, 38, of Escondido. 
Johnson was alone in his l983 Mercedes-Benz driving south on Jesmond Dene Road 
at a high speed when his car failed to ride out the turn, the spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
The car crossed the northbound lanes, struck the tree and overturned. 
</P>
<P>
. 
</P>
</TEXT>
