<HEADLINE>
<P>
AIRPORT A NOISY NEIGHBOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Regarding your story of March 27, perhaps the reason Burbank Airport is losing 
money is because it is no longer a good neighbor. 
</P>
<P>
Since last August, when the airport changed its flight pattern, residents of 
Studio City, Sherman Oaks and Encino have been harassed by its flights. 
</P>
<P>
I can see the planes from my back window. Do you know how low and loud a plane 
is when you can see it? Do you know how much air pollution and noise pollution 
comes from a plane that low? Do you know what it's like to have your 
conversations, TV viewing and peace of mind disturbed by the noise? Do you know 
what it's like not to be able to sleep in past 7 a.m. seven days a week because 
the planes are buzzing your house? 
</P>
<P>
What happens to property values when we try to sell our homes? Would you buy a 
house in the flight pattern of an airport? Developers, think what you could do 
with all that land Burbank Airport is on! 
</P>
<P>
We have wonderful airports in Palmdale and LAX. We have minivans that will pick 
you up at your door, drive you directly to these airports without a bit of 
fuss. 
</P>
<P>
We all live in a valley where the noise resounds. There is enough pollution and 
noise on the ground. If we do not want this to continue or increase, now is the 
time to do something! 
</P>
<P>
GENNY TUBRIDY 
</P>
<P>
Sherman Oaks 
</P>
</TEXT>
