<HEADLINE>
<P>
HERE'S THINKING OF YOU, GRACIE ALLEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Garbled adages and mixed metaphors are always fun, like in "A stitch in time 
saves a pound of cure." 
</P>
<P>
They sound like they should make sense, but they really don't. Gracie Allen 
used to be pretty good at it. 
</P>
<P>
In "Perrier Crisis No Watershed for Evian," Feb. 27, an Evian spokesperson 
says, "We know the shoe could always fall on the other foot." 
</P>
<P>
Gracie would have liked that one. 
</P>
<P>
JOHN J. SCHMIDT 
</P>
<P>
Sherman Oaks 
</P>
</TEXT>
