<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE PRACTICE OF 'OUTING' DRAWS FIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Although the gay and lesbian lifestyles differ greatly from my own, I base my 
acceptance of them on the belief that what goes on between consenting adults is 
their business and not mine. 
</P>
<P>
Now a self-righteous few insist that one's choice of sexual partners is, in 
fact, everyone's business. This same group suggests that anyone whose personal 
conduct or politics do not pass their inspection is a proper target for public 
humiliation, loss of job security and disrupted personal relationships through 
exposure of their sexual preferences. This is progress for the gay community? 
</P>
<P>
Sounds like sexual McCarthyism to me. 
</P>
<P>
ELISABETH MAIN 
</P>
<P>
Woodland Hills 
</P>
</TEXT>
