<HEADLINE>
<P>
HOME BUYERS FAIRS TO GIVE PRICE OUTLOOK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Are home prices heading up or down? 
</P>
<P>
At the Los Angeles Times Home Buyers Fairs, you can hear experts offer their 
forecasts for real es 
</P>
<P>
tate inflation in the coming years. 
</P>
<P>
 -- Industry, government and academic analysts will participate in 
question-and-answer panels that discuss the past, present and future in housing 
values. 
</P>
<P>
 -- Representatives from home price data services and research firms will 
provide information on housing values in specific communities throughout the 
Southland. 
</P>
<P>
 -- Ask experts such as Times' columnist Robert J. Bruss what role inflation 
expectations should play in your decision to buy a home. 
</P>
<P>
The all-day Home Buyers Fairs will be held on May 12 at the Los Angeles County 
Fairgrounds in Pomona, May 19 at the Woodland Hills Marriott Hotel in the San 
Fernando Valley and May 26 at the Anaheim Convention Center in Orange County. 
</P>
