<P>
FINANCIAL AID FOR CAL STATE STUDENTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Minority and disadvantaged students attending any of the 19 California state 
universities have until April 30 to apply for scholarships and internships 
totaling $30,000, administered by the California State University-Real Estate 
&amp; Land Use Institute. 
</P>
<P>
Applicants must be enrolled in a real estate program or major in a program 
oriented toward a real estate career, must be at least a half-time 
undergraduate or a classified graduate student and must have a minimum grade 
point average of 2.25 for undergraduates and 3.0 for graduate students. 
</P>
<P>
Awards are expected to range from $322 to $1,518 and will be distributed by 
August. Applications and additional information: Scholarship Selection 
Committee, CSU-Real Estate &amp; Land Use Institute, 650 University Ave., Suite 
201, Sacramento, Calif. 95825. Telephone: (916) 929-6633. 
</P>
