<HEADLINE>
<P>
GARDENER'S CHECKLIST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
For dedicated gardeners, here are suggestions on what to do in the garden this 
week from the California Assn. of Nurserymen: 
</P>
<P>
Let the kids join in on the fun of gardening. 
</P>
<P>
Quick results can be seen after planting such vegetables as radishes; it keeps 
the kids interested while waiting for other ones to grow. 
</P>
<P>
Check with a nurseryman about proper controls for the pests beginning to awaken 
from their winter nap in your garden. 
</P>
<P>
If the danger of frost is past in your area, you can plant fuchsias, 
pelargoniums and geraniums. 
</P>
<P>
Garden peas, snap peas and snow peas are easy to grow and a delight for the 
cook to use in all sorts of dishes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
