<HEADLINE>
<P>
FAIR WARES FOR DISABLED USERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"Opening Doors to a Better Life," is the theme of Abilities Expo, the nation's 
largest display of products and services for people whose activities are 
physically limited. 
</P>
<P>
Scheduled for Friday, Saturday and next Sunday at the Los Angeles Convention 
Center, the exhibit will feature a special kitchen display of motorized 
cabinets, cooktops and counters that adjust height at the touch of a button. 
</P>
<P>
Ways to make the home environment safer will be demonstrated as will 
voice-activated equipment that turns lights and appliances on and off from a 
distance. 
</P>
<P>
Hours at Abilities Expo are 11 a.m. to 6 p.m., Friday and Saturday, and 11 a.m. 
to 5 p.m. Sunday. Admission is $3. For further information call (619) 944-1122. 
</P>
