<HEADLINE>
<P>
MARITIME MUSEUM NEARS OPENING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Visitors to Fisherman's Wharf in Oxnard will soon be able to peer into the 
past, present and future of sailing. 
</P>
<P>
The Maritime Museum, which began as an idea 25 years ago, will become a reality 
this summer when the doors to the 5,000-square-foot museum open. The building, 
at Channel Islands Boulevard and Victoria Avenue, will house maritime art, ship 
models, computers, a library and video displays. Outside, shipbuilding 
demonstrations wil be offered. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, In top photo, Frank Crane, executive director of the museum, inspects a 
model ship at a warehouse. ALAN HAGMAN / Los Angeles Times; Photo, At left, a 
crew continues work on the museum, which is being overseen by a nonprofit 
group.; Photo, At bottom left, detail of a Mayflower model that will be among 
the exhibits. 
</P>
