<HEADLINE>
<P>
MACK TO COACH ST. BONAVENTURE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jon Mack, Loyola High's track and field coach who also has coached at Alemany 
and Notre Dame, has been hired to coach football at St. Bonaventure in Ventura. 
</P>
<P>
The St. Bonaventure job opened when Damian Wilkerson resigned at the end of the 
season. 
</P>
<P>
Mack has compiled a 63-15-1 record in track since 1982 when he took over the 
Notre Dame job as a 20-year-old college student. Mack, 29, who also worked as 
an assistant football coach at Notre Dame, joined the Alemany staff in 1988 and 
served as track coach and a football assistant. He has filled the same posts 
since joining the Loyola staff last fall. 
</P>
</TEXT>
