<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Slip-Splash He Was Taking a Bath: While searching for tadpoles recently 
in a shallow pond at Douglas Park in Santa Monica, 8-year-old Erik Beck got a 
closer, wetter look than he wanted. He slipped, sprawled, splashed and 
generally got soaked. The pond's bottom was slick with moss, making it 
difficult for his friend Pedro Sanchez, 7, to reach Erik and pull him ashore. 
Eventually, they summoned Erik's mother, Elizabeth Holycross, who managed to 
get a grip on her son and drag him back to the rocky shoreline. JEROME HENKEL / 
For The Times 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wild Art 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA040190-0126 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 197993 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
April 1, 1990, Sunday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Opinion; Part M; Page 1; Column 1; Opinion Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
