<P>
EARLIMART; 
</P>
<P>
NO CONTAMINANTS FOUND IN WELL WATER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and Wire reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
No contaminants have been found in water samples taken from five wells in the 
San Joaquin Valley town of Earlimart where six childhood cancers, all involving 
Latino children, are being investigated, health officials have reported. 
</P>
<P>
Results of state testing of the community's five wells were relayed to the Town 
Council last week, said Jay Johnson, Tulare County environmental health 
specialist. "It sure was some positive news," Johnson said. Some citizens had 
feared chemicals in the water might have triggered the cancers, said the Rev. 
Juan Saavedra, chairman of the Town Council. 
</P>
