<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Derek Knight won both hurdles races and UCLA beat California, 93-69, for the 
Bruins' 21st consecutive dual-meet victory over the Golden Bears. 
</P>
<P>
Cal's last dual victory over UCLA was 76-68 in 1968. 
</P>
<P>
The Bruins are 44-0-1 in dual meets under sixth-year coach Bob Larsen. 
</P>
<P>
Knight won the 110-meter high hurdles in a season-best 14.08 seconds, and the 
400-meter intermediates in 51.79. 
</P>
<P>
Cal's Atlee Mahorn won the 100 meters in 10.37, the 200 in a season-best 20.90 
and anchored the Golden Bears' winning 400-meter relay in a season-best 40.82. 
</P>
<P>
Three Bruins were injured. Olympic gold medalist Steve Lewis, who was winning 
the 400 meters, suffered a pulled right hamstring. Jay Bettinger won the pole 
vault at 16 feet 8 3/4 inches, but suffered a left heel bruise and was on 
crutches after the event. Derrick Baker, who was sixth in the long jump, pulled 
his left hamstring. 
</P>
</TEXT>
