<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: NORRIS KNOCKS OUT MUGABI, TAKES TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Terry Norris floored John Mugabi 90 seconds into the fight and took Mugabi's 
World Boxing Council super welterweight title Saturday with a knockout at 2:47 
of the first round at Tampa, Fla. 
</P>
<P>
Mugabi got up the first time at the count of eight and looked as if he might 
survive the round. But Norris, 153 3/4 pounds, hurt the champion again with a 
straight right and unleashed another right that sent Mugabi down to stay about 
15 seconds later. 
</P>
<P>
Mugabi is 37-3, including 1986 losses to Marvelous Marvin Hagler and Duane 
Thomas. Norris is 25-3 with 14 knockouts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
