</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Allan Leavell, who formerly played for the Houston Rockets of the NBA, was 
cited and released after he allegedly attacked a referee during a Continental 
Basketball Assn. game at Ventura. 
</P>
<P>
Leavell was told to appear in Municipal Court at a later date to face possible 
charges after he allegedly struck referee Pete Quinn Friday night, leaving him 
unconscious for a brief period. 
</P>
<P>
Quinn called a technical foul on Leavell for unsportsmanlike conduct, one of 
the three technicals called against Tulsa. Leavell alleged that Quinn cursed at 
him, Tulsa Coach Henry Bibby said. 
</P>
