found -- likely victims from a camp Soviets used to intern Germans after World 
War II. It was only the latest trauma that freedom has brought East Germans. 
Village resident Kurt Mueller, right, pushed officials to dig up the site. 
"Finally the truth is out," he said. Reuters; Map, Stalinsim victims, Los 
Angeles Times 
</P>
