<HEADLINE>
<P>
MOST VIEWERS WILL HAVE TO WAIT AND SEE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Most Southern Californians won't be able to see the new HA! comedy channel when 
it begins today. Symptomatic of the difficulty that new cable ventures face 
getting off the ground these days, only one cable system in Los Angeles and 
Orange counties is carrying the service: Century Cable -- and only in the areas 
of West Hollywood, Beverly Hills and Marina del Rey. 
</P>
<P>
Paragon Cable, which serves Garden Grove, Huntington Beach, Westminster, 
Fountain Valley, Stanton, Rossmoor, Los Alamitos, Midway City and parts of 
Anaheim, has signed up to carry HA! but it won't start for a month or two, and 
will only be available initially for 12 hours a day, sharing channel space with 
another, as-yet-undecided programming service. 
</P>
<P>
Neither of the major cable systems in San Diego has picked up HA! yet either. 
</P>
