<HEADLINE>
<P>
WRONG CROWD COUNT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Regarding the letter (March 20) on "Meet Your Judges Night," the judges of 
North Orange County Municipal Court want to correct a remark that only about 
100 people showed up: We had more than 200 people in our Spanish-speaking 
courtroom and more than 200 in our English-speaking courtroom, for a total of 
more than 400 people. 
</P>
<P>
The judges of this court were very much pleased that so many people came. We 
have been asked by Loara High School to send a panel of our judges so that 
those young people who could not attend March 6 could ask us questions. 
</P>
<P>
BETTY L. ELIAS, Chairperson 
</P>
