<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP SOFTBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
MATER DEI STREAKING AGAIN, BUT NOT THE RIGHT WAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ANGIE LoSASSO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ANAHEIM 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
It was a tough week for Mater Dei High School, Orange County's top-ranked 
softball team. The Monarchs lost to Thousand Oaks, 2-1, Saturday in the 5-A 
championship game of the Canyon Tournament of Champions. 
</P>
<P>
It was the second loss of the week for Mater Dei, which started the season 
12-0. 
</P>
<P>
Mater Dei fell behind, 1-0, in the second inning on Saturday when Ericka 
Gulbranson scored on a squeeze. Pitcher Terri Kobata fielded the bunt and made 
a perfect throw to catcher Tracy Rice, but a forceful slide jarred the ball out 
of Rice's mitt. 
</P>
<P>
Thousand Oaks scored again in the fourth, when Tricia Gregoire doubled and then 
crossed the plate after a grounder glanced off first baseman Amy Moeller's 
glove and into right field. 
</P>
<P>
"It's a frustrating way to give up a run, but those things (errors) happen," 
Mater Dei Coach Kathy Quesnell said. "They came out aggressive and we have a 
tendency, when we play aggressive teams, to take a step back. We had our 
chances. We had the baserunners. We just can't get them across." 
</P>
<P>
The Monarchs had five hits but left four runners on base. Jennifer Cline's 
single drove in Theresa Conway with Mater Dei's lone run in the fourth. 
</P>
<P>
Kobata (5-2) gave up only three hits and had nine strikeouts. 
</P>
<P>
"Terri is a competitor. She wanted this game," Quesnell said. "Thousand Oaks is 
a good team and they're aggressive, but it's too bad we couldn't back Terri 
up." 
</P>
<P>
Kobata, Rice and Cline were named to the all-tournament team and teammate Amy 
Godwin was named tournament MVP on offense. 
</P>
<P>
In other Canyon tournament games: 
</P>
<P>
Fountain Valley 3, Simi Valley 2 (8 innings) -- Both teams waited until the 
eighth inning to take advantage of the tiebreaker rule and the Barons took home 
the third-place trophy. Fountain Valley's Rae Rice posted her fifth victory 
(5-0). 
</P>
<P>
Los Alamitos 2, Agoura 0 -- Shelley Smith had the game-winning RBI as Los 
Alamitos picked up its 10th victory of the season in the seventh-place game. 
Shannon Skoglund improved to 5-1. 
</P>
<P>
St. Joseph's 5, Huntington Beach 2 -- Kelly Sparks of St. Joseph's went three 
for three with five RBIs to help defeat Huntington Beach (2-7) in the 
ninth-place game. 
</P>
<P>
In nonleague games: 
</P>
<P>
La Habra 2-1, Ocean View 1-4 (first game, 9 innings) -- Three Ocean View 
pitchers combined for a one-hit victory in the nightcap. Marla Pickard got the 
victory with relief help from Tami Dowlin and Jonna Lawson. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Ericka Gulbranson gives Thousand Oaks a 1-0 lead in second inning; she 
knocked the ball out of Mater Dei catcher Terry Rice's hands. CHRISTINE WALTER 
/ Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
