<P>
The networks wonder why they're losing viewers and the answer is simple: Too 
many shows have constant repeats! "thirtysomething" is one of the biggest 
offenders. When the story lines of programs are serialized, it's especially 
difficult for viewers to get back into the series after a few repeats. If the 
networks want a larger audience, they should order more episodes. 
</P>
<P>
Aaron Paquette, San Marino 
