<TEXT>
<P>
It's not enough to see Hal Fishman, Pat Lalama and Warren Olney (et al.) during 
almost every commercial break; we must also put up with a recap of a recap for 
a recap via those obtrusive boxes during the credits of movies shown on KTLA, 
KTTV and KCOP. 
</P>
<P>
Why? I don't know. It's the same news we heard 20 minutes earlier, most of 
which we're already aware of anyway. It's unfortunate enough that most films 
are cut. If that can't be helped, the stations at least can show their film 
libraries a little respect by giving the 10 o'clock newscasts a rest until 10 
o'clock. 
</P>
<P>
R. A. Allen, Inglewood 
